In [102]:
df['score'].fillna(df['score'].median(), inplace = True)
df['score_max'].fillna(df['score_max'].median(), inplace = True)
df['extract'].fillna(df['extract'].mode()[0], inplace = True)
df['author'].fillna(df['author'].mode()[0], inplace = True)
df['product'].fillna(df['product'].mode()[0], inplace = True)

  • score_max: is always 10, dropping it

In [119]:
def popularity_rec(data):
    ratings_mean_count = pd.DataFrame(data.groupby('product')['score'].mean())
    ratings_mean_count['rating_counts'] = data.groupby('product')['score'].count()
    ratings_mean_count = ratings_mean_count.sort_values(by=['score','rating_counts'], ascending=[False, False])
    print('Popularity based top 5 recommend mobile phones.: \n')
    display(ratings_mean_count.head())
    return

KNN Item based

In [128]:
def knn_item(train, test):
    knn_i = KNNWithMeans(k=10, sim_options={'name': 'pearson_baseline', 'user_based': False})
    knn_i.fit(train)
    knn_i_pred = knn_i.test(test)
    return knn_i_pred, knn_i

knn_i_pred, knn_i = knn_item(trainset, testset)
print('RMSE value(Item-based Model, test-set): ', accuracy.rmse(knn_i_pred))
knn_i_rmse = accuracy.rmse(knn_i_pred)

KNN User based

In [129]:
def knn_user(train, test):
    knn_u = KNNWithMeans(k=10, sim_options={'name': 'pearson_baseline', 'user_based': True})
    knn_u.fit(train)
    knn_u_pred = knn_u.test(test)
    return knn_u_pred, knn_u

knn_u_pred, knn_u = knn_user(trainset, testset)
print('RMSE value(User-based Model, test-set): ', accuracy.rmse(knn_u_pred))
knn_u_rmse = accuracy.rmse(knn_u_pred)

In [134]:
from collections import defaultdict
In [135]:
def get_top_n(predictions, n=5):
    top_n = defaultdict(list)
    for uid, iid, true_r, est, _ in predictions:
        top_n[uid].append((iid, est))

    # sorting predictions for each user and retrieving the n highest ones.
    for uid, user_ratings in top_n.items():
        user_ratings.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        top_n[uid] = user_ratings[:n]

    return top_n
In [142]:

Popularity based recommendation systems can be useful in multiple scenarios like:

  • When there is no data about the user and items.
  • When it is required to show most popular items in different categories along with personalized results like:
    • Most popular trending clothes or most popular songs on a website/app
    • Most popular packages for vaccations, or holidays, or trips etc

Giving personalised recommendation to the user, when user history, details or some purchase data is available.
Some examples can be:

  • Personalized movie, web series recommendations - like on OTT platforms as Netflix, Youtube, Amazon Prime

Other from Popularity and Collaborative Filtering

  • hybrid recommendation methods
  • Content Collaborative method
  • Demographic
  • Utility based
  • Knowledge based recommendation system
